13/03/2005
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- During talks with Montenegro's political leadership Friday (11 March), Albanian President Alfred Moisiu praised the level of bilateral co-operation and expressed hope for enhanced ties.
Meeting with Montenegrin counterpart Filip Vujanovic, Moisiu said Tirana wants to boost co-operation in the transport and communications sectors, environmental protection, trade and tourism.
Moisiu also met with Montenegrin Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic.
They discussed issues related to the Serbia-Montenegro federal union and Kosovo's status.
(Albanian government Web site - 11/03/05)
